preds: ['Broke & Bored is a great place to eat. The food is great and the prices are reasonable.', "I've been here a few times now and have always been pleased with the food and service.", 'The food was great, the service was great, and the atmosphere was great.', 'The best place to get a good breakfast in the area.', 'The best buffet in Vegas!', 'Free WiFi, flat-screen TVs, and a pool table are just a few of the amenities you can expect at this hotel.', 'Located in the heart of the Fashion Square Mall, this is a great place to grab a bite to eat.', 'The burgers are average at best.', 'The best pho in town.', 'Las Vegas Strip hotel deals and specials', 'Located in the heart of the city, this hotel is within walking distance of the main shopping area.', 'Located in the heart of the city, this restaurant is a great place to dine in numerous times. The food is good, the staff is really nice and your food arrives really quick. My family and I usually order both sushi and entrées. It was pretty busy today, but the servers were always aware of our drinks running low and knew when we were wrapping things up.', 'Located in the heart of the Fashion Show Mall, this upscale, yet casual eatery offers a wide selection of wines, cheeses, and charcuterie.', 'Located in the heart of the Philadelphia Museum of Art, this museum is a must-see for art lovers.', "Located in the Asian market, this restaurant is family owned and operated. The men who served me reminded me of my own family and I felt at home. It wasn't busy at all when I came in on a Monday afternoon but when I got my pho, it was so good. One thing I always pay attention to when eating pho at restaurants are the noodles. The noodles were freshly cooked and the pho broth was great, but definitely not as good as my dad's (*wink wink wink) hahaha! The man who made my food spoke to me like I was his niece in Vietnamese and it was nice to talk to him, since I don't get much of a chance to speak Vietnamese here in Reno.", 'Located in the heart of downtown, this is a great place to grab a bite to eat.', 'The event was a great opportunity for an evening out, I got to sample some great items, and they had a nice silent auction.', 'Located in the heart of the Las Vegas Strip, the Palms is a great place to stay.', 'The food was good, but the service was terrible.', 'Fat Straw is a trendy, high-end bubble tea cafe in Edgehill Village.', 'The hotel is located in the heart of the city, and is within walking distance of the main shopping area.', "Located in the heart of the Montecito area, Jeannine's is a charming little bakery with amazing food. I arrived around 830A on a Saturday and there were only a few people in line in front of me. Order and pay at the cash register, then seat yourself - coffee was out very quickly and food followed soon enough. I opted for my usual non fat latte and ordered the Famous Banana Kahlua French Toast - Challah bread topped with bananas sauteed in brown sugar, Kahlua and butter - OMG, Wow! Blew me away, sex in your mouth good! Many reviews mentioned this being the best french toast anyone had ever eaten therefore my hopes were set exceptionally high and I will tell you, they were not let down for a second. It's quite hard to compare it to my other most fav french toast (chocolate chip cookie chips ahoy french toast from the Griddle Cafe in LA) because they are quite different so they share the #1 spot ;)"]

preds: ['The best place to stay in Vegas.', 'Gypsy Saloon is a great place to go for happy hour.', 'The best burgers in town!', 'Located in the heart of the downtown area, this restaurant is a great place to grab a bite to eat.', 'The food was good, but the service was a bit slow.', 'I have been to this location several times and have always been pleased with the service and quality of the food.', 'The best place to get a good cup of coffee in the city.', 'The best place to go for a drink and a bite to eat.', 'The Flying V Bar and Grill-offers a delightful respite from Tucson\'s record breaking heat. During my three visits Ryan was manning the bar. A long list of various margarita and cocktails are offered. We enjoyed the Prickley pear and Rojo matgaritas. Ryan is an efficient and interesting local man who tutored us on our first visit with tips about hikes, and activities to see in Tucson. Sitting at the bar is an opportunity to gather information from locals not found on line or in tour books. For instance it is prudent to check the weather forecast when traveling from Tucson to Phoenix for "haboobs". These are intense dust storms that can slow or stop travel. I\'d never heard of such a thing.Flying V is rated high for food and service, a rating deserved. Upon several recommendations we settled on the rack of ribs for dinner to share, along with local vegetables and Caesar salad. All were delivered in shared portions and were excellent. The ribs were fall of the bone tender and tasty. Our server Kelsey was efficient and attentive to our every need. There is an outside dining area overlooking the golf course, but it was too hot to sit outside.', 'The best pizza in town!', 'food.', 'Cider and yoga were happening the day I was there and I was sad to be visiting from out of town and not have the appropriate gear with me. It feels like there was always something going on here. The ciders were all delicious and I wished I was in a position to take more home. I ordered a flight, sat back on the sofa and sipped while I read a book.', 'The best place to eat in the area.', 'The best place to get a good burger in the area.', 'The best place to stay in Vegas', 'The best burgers in town.', 'The best burgers in town.', 'The best place to get a good cup of coffee in the city.', 'Great place for a family meal.', 'The hotel is located in the heart of the city, in the midst of the shopping and entertainment district.', "Wasabi2 is a sushi spot in a shopping center!! Something you don't see just all the time. All jokes aside, I think Wasabi2 has some of the best, reasonably priced sushi/sashimi around. The employee who answers the phone every time I order is so freaking friendly, I address him by his first name when I go pick up my food. One time I got a free calendar and it was pretty hilarious to watch 6 of my family members look at their zodiac symbol and argue whether they do or don't fit the traits of their cosmic sign. One thing we can't argue is how consistently good this sushi spot is.", "Beiler's Bakery is a great place to grab a quick snack or a large dessert."]
